{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869974980,"sessionID":"ses_285e719caffed1lsPrEfzDjxoJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a194f18001EeTWpjqlVsn5Vo","messageID":"msg_d7a19337a0015hIeG51zbtcCY5","sessionID":"ses_285e719caffed1lsPrEfzDjxoJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-34d1b9adf1c340948cffba03dd1bc237","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status Commands Design Document\n2: \n3: **AR**: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令  \n4: **Module**: cmd/cli  \n5: **Language**: Python  \n6: **Size**: M\n7: \n8: ## Overview\n9: \n10: The `invoke` and `status` commands are essential components of the AgentCube CLI that enable users to interact with deployed AI agents. The `invoke` command sends requests to published agent endpoints with optional payloads and custom headers, while the `status` command provides visibility into agent deployment state and health. Both commands support multiple providers: the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service).\n11: \n12: ## Background\n13: \n14: AgentCube users need to interact with their deployed AI agents after the publish process completes. This includes:\n15: \n16: 1. **Invocation**: Sending requests to agents with custom payloads, managing session IDs, and receiving responses\n17: 2. **Status Monitoring**: Checking deployment health, endpoint availability, and runtime status\n18: 3. **Multi-provider Support**: Working with both AgentCube CRs and standard Kubernetes deployments\n19: 4. **Flexible Configuration**: Supporting custom headers, different payload formats, and provider-specific options\n20: \n21: The invoke/status commands complete the lifecycle management flow (pack → build → publish → invoke → status), providing users with full control over their AI agents.\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### Component Diagram\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────┐\n29: │   CLI (Typer)   │\n30: │  main.py     │\n31: └──────┬──────┘\n32:        │\n33:        ├──► invoke() ───► InvokeRuntime ───► HTTP Client\n34:        │                  invoke_runtime.py         │\n35:        │                                            ├──► AgentCube Provider (CR)\n36:        │                                            └──► Direct HTTP (K8s Service)\n37:        │\n38:        └──► status() ───► StatusRuntime ───► K8s Client\n39:                           status_runtime.py         │\n40:                                                    ├──► AgentRuntime CR Status\n41:                                                    └──► Deployment/Service Status\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Layer Architecture\n45: \n46: ```\n47: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n48: │         CLI Layer (agentcube/cli/main.py)    │\n49: │  • Typer command definitions               │\n50: │  • User input validation                   │\n51: │  • Rich output formatting                  │\n52: │  • Error handling and user feedback        │\n53: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n54:                     │\n55:                     ▼\n56: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n57: │     Runtime Layer (agentcube/runtime/)     │\n58: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │\n59: │  │  InvokeRuntime  │  │  StatusRuntime  │  │\n60: │  │  invoke_runtime.py││ status_runtime.py│  │\n61: │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │\n62: │  • Command orchestration                   │\n63: │  • Provider selection                      │\n64: │  • Session management                      │\n65: │  • Endpoint resolution                     │\n66: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n67:                     │\n68:                     ▼\n69: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n70: │      Service Layer (agentcube/services/)   │\n71: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  │\n72: │  │AgentCubeProvider│  │KubernetesProvider│ │\n73: │  │agentcube_       │  │k8s_provider.py  │  │\n74: │  │provider.py      │  │                 │  │\n75: │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  │\n76: │  • AgentRuntime CR operations              │\n77: │  • K8s Deployment/Service operations       │\n78: │  • Metadata management                     │\n79: │  • Status aggregation                      │\n80: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n81:                     │\n82:                     ▼\n83: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n84: │    HTTP / K8s Client Layer                  │\n85: │  • httpx.AsyncClient (async HTTP requests) │\n86: │  • kubernetes.KubernetesClient (K8s API)   │\n87: └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Key Components\n91: \n92: 1. **CLI Layer** (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n93:    - `invoke()`: Typer command for invoking agents\n94:    - `status()`: Typer command for checking agent status\n95:    - Payload and header parsing\n96:    - Provider selection\n97:    - Rich table formatting for status output\n98: \n99: 2. **Runtime Layer**\n100:    - `InvokeRuntime`: Orchestration of agent invocation\n101:    - `StatusRuntime`: Aggregation of deployment status\n102:    - Provider abstraction (AgentCube vs K8s)\n103:    - Session ID management\n104: \n105: 3. **Service Layer**\n106:    - `AgentCubeProvider`: AgentRuntime CR operations\n107:    - `KubernetesProvider`: Standard K8s deployment operations\n108:    - `MetadataService`: Loading workspace metadata\n109: \n110: 4. **Data Plane Clients** (from Python SDK)\n111:    - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: HTTP communication with agents\n112:    - Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n113: \n114: ## Data Structures\n115: \n116: ### InvokeOptions\n117: \n118: Dictionary containing invoke command options:\n119: \n120: ```python\n121: {\n122:     \"workspace\": str,                          # Path to workspace (default: \".\")\n123:     \"payload\": Dict[str, Any],                 # JSON payload for agent\n124:     \"headers\": Optional[Dict[str, str]],       # Custom HTTP headers\n125:     \"provider\": str,                           # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\" (default: \"agentcube\")\n126:     \"verbose\": bool,                           # Enable verbose logging\n127: }\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### StatusOptions\n131: \n132: Dictionary containing status command options:\n133: \n134: ```python\n135: {\n136:     \"workspace\": str,                          # Path to workspace (default: \".\")\n137:     \"provider\": str,                           # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\" (default: \"agentcube\")\n138:     \"verbose\": bool,                           # Enable verbose logging\n139: }\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### AgentMetadata Fields (Invoke/Status-related)\n143: \n144: Relevant fields from `AgentMetadata` for invoke/status operations:\n145: \n146: ```python\n147: agent_name: str                          # Agent identifier\n148: agent_id: Optional[str]                  # Agent ID assigned by AgentCube\n149: agent_endpoint: Optional[str]            # Published agent endpoint URL\n150: session_id: Optional[str]                # Current session ID for invoke\n151: k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] # K8s deployment information\n152: router_url: Optional[str]                # Router URL for AgentCube provider\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### K8sDeploymentInfo\n156: \n157: Structure for standard K8s deployment information:\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: {\n161:     \"type\": str,                          # \"Deployment\" or \"AgentRuntime\"\n162:     \"namespace\": str,                     # K8s namespace\n163:     \"name\": str,                          # Deployment or CR name\n164:     \"replicas\": int,                      # Number of replicas\n165:     \"available_replicas\": Optional[int],  # Available replicas (K8s)\n166:     \"service_url\": str,                   # Service endpoint URL\n167:     \"node_port\": Optional[int],           # NodePort for K8s Service\n168: }\n169: ```\n170: \n171: ### StatusResult\n172: \n173: Structure for aggregated status information:\n174: \n175: ```python\n176: {\n177:     \"status\": str,                        # \"running\", \"not_published\", \"error\", etc.\n178:     \"agent_name\": str,                    # Agent name\n179:     \"agent_id\": Optional[str],            # Agent ID (AgentCube provider)\n180:     \"endpoint\": str,                      # Agent endpoint URL\n181:     \"deployment\": Optional[K8sDeploymentInfo],  # Deployment details\n182:     \"error\": Optional[str],               # Error message if status is \"error\"\n183:     \"namespace\": str,                     # K8s namespace\n184: }\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ## API Contracts\n188: \n189: ### InvokeRuntime()\n190: \n191: ```python\n192: def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n193:     \"\"\"\n194:     Initialize InvokeRuntime.\n195: \n196:     Args:\n197:         verbose: Enable verbose logging\n198:         provider: Target provider (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n199:     \"\"\"\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: def invoke(\n206:     self,\n207:     workspace_path: Path,\n208:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n209:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n210: ) -> Any:\n211:     \"\"\"\n212:     Invoke a deployed agent with a payload.\n213: \n214:     Args:\n215:         workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n216:         payload: JSON payload to send to agent\n217:         headers: Optional custom HTTP headers\n218: \n219:     Returns:\n220:         Agent response (JSON or raw data)\n221: \n222:     Raises:\n223:         ValueError: If prerequisites not met (not published, invalid endpoint)\n224:         RuntimeError: If invocation fails or endpoint unreachable\n225:         FileNotFoundError: If metadata file not found\n226:     \"\"\"\n227: ```\n228: \n229: **Behavior**:\n230: 1. Load metadata from workspace\n231: 2. Validate invoke prerequisites (agent_id or endpoint exists)\n232: 3. Resolve endpoint based on provider and deployment type\n233: 4. Initialize data plane client with session management\n234: 5. Send HTTP POST request with payload and headers\n235: 6. Parse and return response\n236: \n237: ### InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n238: \n239: ```python\n240: def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n241:     self,\n242:     workspace_path: Path\n243: ) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n244:     \"\"\"\n245:     Validate that agent is published and extract metadata.\n246: \n247:     Args:\n248:         workspace_path: Path to workspace\n249: \n250:     Returns:\n251:         Tuple of (metadata, endpoint, agent_name)\n252: \n253:     Raises:\n254:         ValueError: If agent not published or endpoint not found\n255:         FileNotFoundError: If metadata file not found\n256:     \"\"\"\n257: ```\n258: \n259: **Validation Checks**:\n260: 1. Metadata file exists in workspace\n261: 2. Agent is published (has `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint`)\n262: 3. Endpoint is reachable and valid URL\n263: \n264: ### InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n265: \n266: ```python\n267: async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n268:     self,\n269:     agent_id: str,\n270:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n271:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n272:     endpoint: str,\n273:     workspace_path: Path\n274: ) -> Any:\n275:     \"\"\"\n276:     Invoke agent using AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR).\n277: \n278:     Args:\n279:         agent_id: Agent ID from metadata\n280:         payload: Request payload\n281:         headers: Custom headers\n282:         endpoint: Base endpoint URL\n283:         workspace_path: Path to workspace (for metadata access)\n284: \n285:     Returns:\n286:         Agent response\n287: \n288:     Raises:\n289:         RuntimeError: If invocation fails\n290:     \"\"\"\n291: ```\n292: \n293: **Behavior**:\n294: - Constructs AgentRuntime invocation URL: `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n295: - Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` for async HTTP request\n296: - Adds session header if `session_id` in metadata\n297: - Merges custom headers\n298: - Sends POST request with JSON payload\n299: - Returns parsed JSON response\n300: \n301: ### InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation()\n302: \n303: ```python\n304: async def _direct_http_invocation(\n305:     self,\n306:     endpoint: str,\n307:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n308:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n309:     workspace_path: Path\n310: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n311:     \"\"\"\n312:     Direct HTTP invocation to agent endpoint (K8s Service).\n313: \n314:     Args:\n315:         endpoint: Full endpoint URL\n316:         payload: Request payload\n317:         headers: Custom headers\n318:         workspace_path: Path to workspace\n319: \n320:     Returns:\n321:         Agent response as dictionary\n322: \n323:     Raises:\n324:         RuntimeError: If HTTP request fails\n325:     \"\"\"\n326: ```\n327: \n328: **Behavior**:\n329: - Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` for async HTTP request\n330: - Adds session header if `session_id` in metadata\n331: - Merges custom headers\n332: - Sends POST request with JSON payload\n333: - Returns parsed JSON response\n334: \n335: ### StatusRuntime()\n336: \n337: ```python\n338: def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n339:     \"\"\"\n340:     Initialize StatusRuntime.\n341: \n342:     Args:\n343:         verbose: Enable verbose logging\n344:         provider: Target provider (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n345:     \"\"\"\n346: ```\n347: \n348: ### StatusRuntime.get_status()\n349: \n350: ```python\n351: def get_status(\n352:     self,\n353:     workspace_path: Path,\n354:     provider: Optional[str] = None\n355: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n356:     \"\"\"\n357:     Get the status of a deployed agent.\n358: \n359:     Args:\n360:         workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n361:         provider: Optional provider override (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n362: \n363:     Returns:\n364:         StatusResult dictionary with deployment status\n365: \n366:     Raises:\n367:         FileNotFoundError: If metadata file not found\n368:         RuntimeError: If status check fails\n369:     \"\"\"\n370: ```\n371: \n372: **Behavior**:\n373: 1. Load metadata from workspace\n374: 2. Check if agent is published\n375: 3. Determine provider (from argument or metadata)\n376: 4. Query provider-specific status\n377: 5. Aggregate status information\n378: 6. Return status result\n379: \n380: ### StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()\n381: \n382: ```python\n383: def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n384:     \"\"\"\n385:     Get status for standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service.\n386: \n387:     Args:\n388:         metadata: Agent metadata with deployment information\n389: \n390:     Returns:\n391:         StatusResult dictionary\n392: \n393:     Raises:\n394:         RuntimeError: If K8s API query fails\n395:     \"\"\"\n396: ```\n397: \n398: **Behavior**:\n399: - Uses `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n400: - Queries Deployment status (replicas, available_replicas)\n401: - Queries Service status (NodePort, endpoints)\n402: - Aggregates into status result\n403: - Determines overall status: \"running\", \"pending\", \"error\"\n404: \n405: ### StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()\n406: \n407: ```python\n408: def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n409:     \"\"\"\n410:     Get status for AgentCube AgentRuntime CR.\n411: \n412:     Args:\n413:         metadata: Agent metadata with CR information\n414: \n415:     Returns:\n416:         StatusResult dictionary\n417: \n418:     Raises:\n419:         RuntimeError: If CR query fails\n420:     \"\"\"\n421: ```\n422: \n423: **Behavior**:\n424: - Uses `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()`\n425: - Queries AgentRuntime custom resource\n426: - Extracts status from CR `.status` field\n427: - Checks `agentEndpoint` for availability\n428: - Determines overall status: \"running\", \"created_no_status\", \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"error\"\n429: \n430: ### CLI Layer Functions\n431: \n432: #### main.invoke()\n433: \n434: ```python\n435: def invoke(\n436:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n437:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n438:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n439:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n440:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n441: ) -> None:\n442:     \"\"\"\n443:     Invoke a published agent with a JSON payload.\n444:     \"\"\"\n445: ```\n446: \n447: **Behavior**:\n448: 1. Parse payload JSON (exit with error if invalid)\n449: 2. Parse headers from `--header` arguments (format: `key:value`)\n450: 3. Initialize `InvokeRuntime` with provider\n451: 4. Call `runtime.invoke()` with workspace, payload, headers\n452: 5. Display result using Rich console\n453: 6. Handle errors with `_handle_error()`\n454: \n455: #### main.status()\n456: \n457: ```python\n458: def status(\n459:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n460:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n461:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n462: ) -> None:\n463:     \"\"\"\n464:     Check the status of a published agent.\n465:     \"\"\"\n466: ```\n467: \n468: **Behavior**:\n469: 1. Initialize `StatusRuntime` with provider\n470: 2. Call `runtime.get_status()` with workspace\n471: 3. Display status in Rich table format\n472: 4. Exit with code 1 if status is \"not_published\" or \"error\"\n473: 5. Handle errors with `_handle_error()`\n474: \n475: ## Error Handling\n476: \n477: ### Error Hierarchy\n478: \n479: ```\n480: Exception\n481: ├── ValueError (User input/prerequisite errors)\n482: │   ├── \"Invalid JSON payload: {error}\"\n483: │   ├── \"Invalid header format: {header}. Expected 'key:value'\"\n484: │   ├── \"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\"\n485: │   ├── \"No agent endpoint found in metadata\"\n486: │   └── \"Both router_url and workload_manager_url must be configured in metadata for provider=agentcube\"\n487: ├── RuntimeError (System/runtime errors)\n488: │   ├── \"Failed to invoke agent: {error}\"\n489: │   ├── \"Agent endpoint not reachable: {endpoint}\"\n490: │   ├── \"Failed to get agent status: {error}\"\n491: │   ├── \"AgentRuntime not found in Kubernetes\"\n492: │   └── \"Kubernetes API error: {error}\"\n493: ├── httpx.HTTPError (HTTP errors)\n494: │   ├── Connection errors\n495: │   ├── Timeout errors\n496: │   └── HTTP status errors (4xx, 5xx)\n497: └── FileNotFoundError\n498:     └── \"No metadata file found in {workspace}\"\n499: ```\n500: \n501: ### Error Handling Strategy\n502: \n503: #### CLI Layer Payload Validation\n504: \n505: ```python\n506: def invoke(...):\n507:     # Validate payload JSON\n508:     try:\n509:         payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n510:     except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n511:         console.print(f\"[red]Invalid JSON payload: {e}[/red]\")\n512:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n513:     \n514:     # Validate headers format\n515:     headers = {}\n516:     if header_list:\n517:         for header in header_list:\n518:             if ':' not in header:\n519:                 console.print(f\"[red]Invalid header format: {header}. Expected 'key:value'[/red]\")\n520:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n521:             key, value = header.split(':', 1)\n522:             headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n523:     \n524:     # Proceed with invocation\n525:     try:\n526:         runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n527:         result = runtime.invoke(workspace_path, payload_dict, headers)\n528:         display_result(result)\n529:     except Exception as e:\n530:         _handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)\n531: ```\n532: \n533: #### InvokeRuntime Error Handling\n534: \n535: ```python\n536: def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n537:     try:\n538:         metadata, endpoint, agent_name = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n539:         \n540:         # Async invocation\n541:         result = asyncio.run(self._execute_invoke(metadata, endpoint, payload, headers))\n542:         return result\n543:     except ValueError as e:\n544:         raise  # Re-raise user input errors\n545:     except httpx.HTTPError as e:\n546:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to invoke agent: {e}\") from e\n547:     except Exception as e:\n548:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to invoke agent: {e}\") from e\n549: ```\n550: \n551: #### StatusRuntime Error Handling\n552: \n553: ```python\n554: def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n555:     try:\n556:         metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n557:         \n558:         if not metadata.agent_id and not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n559:             return {\n560:                 \"status\": \"not_published\",\n561:                 \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n562:                 \"message\": \"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\"\n563:             }\n564:         \n565:         # Provider-specific status\n566:         resolved_provider = provider or \"agentcube\"\n567:         if resolved_provider == \"agentcube\":\n568:             return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n569:         else:\n570:             return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n571:     except FileNotFoundError as e:\n572:         raise\n573:     except Exception as e:\n574:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to get agent status: {e}\") from e\n575: ```\n576: \n577: #### HTTP Error Handling with Retries\n578: \n579: ```python\n580: async def _http_post_with_retry(self, url: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Dict[str, str], max_retries: int = 3) -> Any:\n581:     retry_count = 0\n582:     last_error = None\n583:     \n584:     while retry_count < max_retries:\n585:         try:\n586:             async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=self.timeout) as client:\n587:                 response = await client.post(url, json=payload, headers=headers)\n588:                 response.raise_for_status()\n589:                 return response.json()\n590:         except httpx.ConnectError as e:\n591:             last_error = e\n592:             retry_count += 1\n593:             if retry_count < max_retries:\n594:                 await asyncio.sleep(2 ** retry_count)  # Exponential backoff\n595:         except httpx.HTTPStatusError as e:\n596:             if e.response.status_code >= 500 and retry_count < max_retries:\n597:                 last_error = e\n598:                 retry_count += 1\n599:                 await asyncio.sleep(2 ** retry_count)\n600:             else:\n601:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"HTTP {e.response.status_code}: {e.response.text}\") from e\n602:     \n603:     raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to connect to agent endpoint after {max_retries} retries: {last_error}\")\n604: ```\n605: \n606: ### User-Facing Error Messages\n607: \n608: | Error | Message | Exit Code |\n609: |-------|---------|-----------|\n610: | Invalid JSON payload | \"Invalid JSON payload: {error}\" | 1 |\n611: | Invalid header format | \"Invalid header format: {header}. Expected 'key:value'\" | 1 |\n612: | Agent not published | \"Error invoking agent: Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\" | 1 |\n613: | No endpoint | \"Error invoking agent: No agent endpoint found in metadata\" | 1 |\n614: | Connection failed | \"Error invoking agent: Failed to connect to agent endpoint: {endpoint}\" | 1 |\n615: | HTTP error | \"Error invoking agent: HTTP {status}: {message}\" | 1 |\n616: | Status not published | \"Error checking status: Agent not published. Run 'publish' first.\" | 1 |\n617: | CR not found | \"Error checking status: AgentRuntime not found in Kubernetes\" | 1 |\n618: \n619: ## Testing Strategy\n620: \n621: ### Unit Tests\n622: \n623: #### Test: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n624: \n625: ```python\n626: def test_validate_success_with_agent_id(tmp_path):\n627:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n628:         \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\\nagent_endpoint: http://localhost:8080\"\n629:     )\n630:     runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n631:     metadata, endpoint, name = runtime._validate_invoke_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n632:     assert metadata.agent_id == \"abc123\"\n633:     assert endpoint == \"http://localhost:8080\"\n634:     assert name == \"test\"\n635: \n636: def test_validate_not_published(tmp_path):\n637:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n638:         \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\"\n639:     )\n640:     runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n641:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Agent not published\"):\n642:         runtime._validate_invoke_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n643: \n644: def test_validate_no_endpoint(tmp_path):\n645:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n646:         \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\"\n647:     )\n648:     runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n649:     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"No agent endpoint found\"):\n650:         runtime._validate_invoke_prerequisites(tmp_path)\n651: ```\n652: \n653: #### Test: StatusRuntime.get_status() - Not Published\n654: \n655: ```python\n656: def test_status_not_published(tmp_path):\n657:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n658:         \"agent_name: test\\nentrypoint: python main.py\"\n659:     )\n660:     runtime = StatusRuntime()\n661:     status = runtime.get_status(tmp_path)\n662:     assert status[\"status\"] == \"not_published\"\n663:     assert \"not published\" in status[\"message\"].lower()\n664: ```\n665: \n666: #### Test: StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()\n667: \n668: ```python\n669: def test_cr_status_running(mocker):\n670:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n671:         agent_name=\"test\",\n672:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n673:         agent_id=\"abc123\",\n674:         k8s_deployment={\n675:             \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n676:             \"name\": \"test\",\n677:             \"namespace\": \"default\"\n678:         }\n679:     )\n680:     runtime = StatusRuntime()\n681:     \n682:     mock_provider = mocker.MagicMock()\n683:     mock_provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n684:         \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test\"},\n685:         \"status\": {\n686:             \"phase\": \"Running\",\n687:             \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://localhost:8080\"\n688:         }\n689:     }\n690:     runtime.agentcube_provider = mock_provider\n691:     \n692:     status = runtime._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n693:     assert status[\"status\"] == \"running\"\n694:     assert status[\"endpoint\"] == \"http://localhost:8080\"\n695: \n696: def test_cr_status_not_found(mocker):\n697:     metadata = AgentMetadata(\n698:         agent_name=\"test\",\n699:         entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n700:         agent_id=\"abc123\",\n701:         k8s_deployment={\n702:             \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n703:             \"name\": \"test\",\n704:             \"namespace\": \"default\"\n705:         }\n706:     )\n707:     runtime = StatusRuntime()\n708:     \n709:     mock_provider = mocker.MagicMock()\n710:     mock_provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = None\n711:     runtime.agentcube_provider = mock_provider\n712:     \n713:     status = runtime._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n714:     assert status[\"status\"] == \"not_found_in_k8s\"\n715: ```\n716: \n717: #### Test: CLI Payload Parsing\n718: \n719: ```python\n720: def test_invoke_valid_json():\n721:     # Test with valid JSON payload\n722:     payload_str = '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'\n723:     payload_dict = json.loads(payload_str)\n724:     assert payload_dict == {\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}\n725: \n726: def test_invoke_invalid_json():\n727:     # Test with invalid JSON payload\n728:     payload_str = '{\"message\": \"hello\", count: 5}'\n729:     with pytest.raises(json.JSONDecodeError):\n730:         json.loads(payload_str)\n731: \n732: def test_invoke_headers_parsing():\n733:     # Test header parsing\n734:     header_list = [\"Authorization: Bearer token123\", \"Content-Type: application/json\"]\n735:     headers = {}\n736:     for header in header_list:\n737:         key, value = header.split(':', 1)\n738:         headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n739:     assert headers == {\n740:         \"Authorization\": \"Bearer token123\",\n741:         \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n742:     }\n743: ```\n744: \n745: ### Integration Tests\n746: \n747: #### Test: End-to-End Invoke (Mocked)\n748: \n749: ```python\n750: @pytest.mark.integration\n751: def test_e2e_invoke_agent(tmp_path, mocker):\n752:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n753:         \"agent_name: test-agent\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\\nagent_endpoint: http://localhost:8080\\nsession_id: session123\"\n754:     )\n755:     \n756:     runtime = InvokeRuntime()\n757:     \n758:     # Mock HTTP client\n759:     mock_response = mocker.MagicMock()\n760:     mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test response\"}\n761:     mock_response.raise_for_status = mocker.MagicMock()\n762:     \n763:     mock_client = mocker.patch(\"httpx.AsyncClient\")\n764:     mock_client.return_value.__aenter__.return_value.post.return_value = mock_response\n765:     \n766:     payload = {\"message\": \"hello\"}\n767:     headers = {\"X-Custom-Header\": \"value\"}\n768:     \n769:     result = runtime.invoke(tmp_path, payload, headers)\n770:     assert result == {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": \"test response\"}\n771: ```\n772: \n773: #### Test: End-to-End Status (Mocked K8s)\n774: \n775: ```python\n776: @pytest.mark.integration\n777: def test_e2e_status_k8s(tmp_path, mocker):\n778:     tmp_path.joinpath(\"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n779:         \"agent_name: test-agent\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nagent_id: abc123\\nk8s_deployment:\\n  type: Deployment\\n  name: test-agent\\n  namespace: default\\n  replicas: 2\\n  service_url: http://localhost:30080\\n\"\n780:     )\n781:     \n782:     runtime = StatusRuntime(provider=\"k8s\")\n783:     \n784:     # Mock K8s provider\n785:     mock_status = {\n786:         \"status\": \"running\",\n787:         \"agent_name\": \"test-agent\",\n788:         \"endpoint\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n789:         \"deployment\": {\n790:             \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n791:             \"name\": \"test-agent\",\n792:             \"namespace\": \"default\",\n793:             \"replicas\": 2,\n794:             \"available_replicas\": 2,\n795:             \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n796:         }\n797:     }\n798:     \n799:     mocker.patch.object(runtime, \"_get_k8s_status\", return_value=mock_status)\n800:     \n801:     status = runtime.get_status(tmp_path)\n802:     assert status[\"status\"] == \"running\"\n803:     assert status[\"deployment\"][\"available_replicas\"] == 2\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ### Mocking Strategy\n807: \n808: #### HTTP Client Mock\n809: \n810: ```python\n811: @pytest.fixture\n812: def mock_http_client(mocker):\n813:     client = mocker.MagicMock(spec=httpx.AsyncClient)\n814:     \n815:     async def mock_post(url, json=None, headers=None, timeout=None):\n816:         response = mocker.MagicMock()\n817:         response.status_code = 200\n818:         response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n819:         response.raise_for_status = mocker.MagicMock()\n820:         return response\n821:     \n822:     client.post = mock_post\n823:     return client\n824: ```\n825: \n826: #### Kubernetes Provider Mock\n827: \n828: ```python\n829: @pytest.fixture\n830: def mock_k8s_provider(mocker):\n831:     provider = mocker.MagicMock(spec=KubernetesProvider)\n832:     provider.get_agent_status.return_value = {\n833:         \"status\": \"running\",\n834:         \"deployment\": {\n835:             \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n836:             \"name\": \"test-agent\",\n837:             \"namespace\": \"default\",\n838:             \"replicas\": 2,\n839:             \"available_replicas\": 2,\n840:         }\n841:     }\n842:     return provider\n843: ```\n844: \n845: #### AgentCube Provider Mock\n846: \n847: ```python\n848: @pytest.fixture\n849: def mock_agentcube_provider(mocker):\n850:     provider = mocker.MagicMock(spec=AgentCubeProvider)\n851:     provider.get_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n852:         \"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test-agent\"},\n853:         \"status\": {\n854:             \"phase\": \"Running\",\n855:             \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://localhost:8080\"\n856:         }\n857:     }\n858:     return provider\n859: ```\n860: \n861: ### Test Coverage Goals\n862: \n863: | Component | Target Coverage |\n864: |-----------|-----------------|\n865: | invoke_runtime.py | 85%+ |\n866: | status_runtime.py | 85%+ |\n867: | main.py (invoke/status commands) | 80%+ |\n868: | agentcube_provider.py | 80%+ (status methods) |\n869: | k8s_provider.py | 80%+ (status methods) |\n870: \n871: ### Test Execution\n872: \n873: ```bash\n874: # Run all tests\n875: pytest tests/\n876: \n877: # Run with coverage\n878: pytest --cov=agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime --cov=agentcube.runtime.status_runtime\n879: \n880: # Run integration tests only\n881: pytest -m integration\n882: \n883: # Run unit tests only\n884: pytest -m \"not integration\"\n885: \n886: # Run specific test file\n887: pytest tests/test_invoke_runtime.py\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ## CLI Usage\n891: \n892: ### Invoke Command\n893: \n894: #### Basic Usage\n895: \n896: ```bash\n897: # Invoke with default payload ({})\n898: kubectl-agentcube invoke\n899: \n900: # Invoke with custom payload\n901: kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'\n902: \n903: # Invoke with custom headers\n904: kubectl-agentcube invoke --header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\" --header \"X-Custom-Header: value\"\n905: \n906: # Invoke with verbose output\n907: kubectl-agentcube invoke --verbose\n908: \n909: # Invoke specific workspace\n910: kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /path/to/workspace\n911: \n912: # Invoke with K8s provider\n913: kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider k8s\n914: ```\n915: \n916: #### Complex Payload Example\n917: \n918: ```bash\n919: kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\n920:   \"query\": \"What is the weather today?\",\n921:   \"context\": {\n922:     \"location\": \"San Francisco\",\n923:     \"date\": \"2024-01-15\"\n924:   },\n925:   \"options\": {\n926:     \"temperature_unit\": \"fahrenheit\"\n927:   }\n928: }' --header \"X-API-Key: your-api-key\"\n929: ```\n930: \n931: ### Status Command\n932: \n933: #### Basic Usage\n934: \n935: ```bash\n936: # Check status of agent in current workspace\n937: kubectl-agentcube status\n938: \n939: # Check status of specific workspace\n940: kubectl-agentcube status -f /path/to/workspace\n941: \n942: # Check status with K8s provider\n943: kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s\n944: \n945: # Check status with verbose output\n946: kubectl-agentcube status --verbose\n947: ```\n948: \n949: ### Prerequisites\n950: \n951: 1. **For invoke**:\n952:    - Agent must be published (run `publish` first)\n953:    - Agent endpoint must be reachable\n954:    - Valid metadata file must exist\n955: \n956: 2. **For status**:\n957:    - Agent must be published (or at least have metadata)\n958:    - Kubernetes access configured (for provider checks)\n959: \n960: ### Output Examples\n961: \n962: #### Invoke Success Output\n963: \n964: ```\n965: ✓ Agent invoked successfully\n966:   Response: {\"result\": \"success\", \"data\": {\"answer\": \"The weather is sunny.\"}}\n967: ```\n968: \n969: #### Status Success Output (AgentCube Provider)\n970: \n971: ```\n972: ┏━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┳━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\n973: ┃ Field              ┃ Value                              ┃\n974: ┡━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━╇━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\n975: │ Status             │ running                            │\n976: │ Agent Name         │ test-agent                         │\n977: │ Agent ID           │ abc123                             │\n978: │ Endpoint           │ http://localhost:8080              │\n979: │ Namespace          │ default                            │\n980: │ Deployment Type    │ AgentRuntime CR                    │\n981: └────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘\n982: ```\n983: \n984: #### Status Success Output (K8s Provider)\n985: \n986: ```\n987: ┏━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┳━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┓\n988: ┃ Field              ┃ Value                              ┃\n989: ┡━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━╇━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┩\n990: │ Status             │ running                            │\n991: │ Agent Name         │ test-agent                         │\n992: │ Endpoint           │ http://localhost:30080             │\n993: │ Namespace          │ default                            │\n994: │ Deployment Type    │ Deployment                         │\n995: │ Replicas           │ 2/2                                │\n996: │ Service URL        │ http://localhost:30080             │\n997: └────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────┘\n998: ```\n999: \n1000: #### Status Not Published Output\n1001: \n1002: ```\n1003: ✗ Agent not published\n1004:   Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' to deploy your agent.\n1005: ```\n1006: \n1007: ## Dependencies\n1008: \n1009: ### Required\n1010: \n1011: - `httpx>=0.24.0`: Async HTTP client for agent invocation\n1012: - `pydantic>=2.0.0`: Data validation (via AgentMetadata)\n1013: - `pyyaml>=6.0.0`: YAML parsing (via MetadataService)\n1014: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0`: CLI framework\n1015: - `rich>=13.0.0`: Rich terminal output formatting\n1016: \n1017: ### Optional\n1018: \n1019: - `kubernetes>=28.0.0`: Kubernetes client for K8s provider status checks\n1020: \n1021: ### External Dependencies\n1022: \n1023: - **Docker**: For local builds (not required for invoke/status)\n1024: - **Kubernetes cluster**: For provider-based deployments\n1025: - **AgentCube runtime**: For AgentRuntime CR support\n1026: \n1027: ## Future Enhancements\n1028: \n1029: 1. **Streaming Responses**: Support for streaming responses from agents (Server-Sent Events, WebSocket)\n1030: 2. **Interactive Mode**: REPL-like interactive session with agents\n1031: 3. **Batch Invocation**: Invoke multiple agents in parallel\n1032: 4. **Response Formatting**: Multiple output formats (JSON, YAML, table)\n1033: 5. **History Tracking**: Track invocation history and responses\n1034: 6. **Session Management**: Enhanced session lifecycle control (create, list, delete sessions)\n1035: 7. **Timeout Control**: Configurable timeout per invocation\n1036: 8. **Retry Strategy**: Configurable retry policies for failed invocations\n1037: 9. **Status Filtering**: Filter status by namespace, labels, or other criteria\n1038: 10. **Status Watch**: Watch mode for real-time status updates\n1039: 11. **Metrics Collection**: Collect and display invocation metrics (latency, success rate)\n1040: 12. **Webhook Support**: Invoke agents via webhooks with automatic routing\n1041: 13. **Payload Templates**: Support for payload templates and variable substitution\n1042: 14. **Multi-region Support**: Invoke agents deployed in multiple regions\n1043: 15. **Load Balancing**: Distribute invocations across multiple agent instances\n1044: \n1045: ## Security Considerations\n1046: \n1047: 1. **Authentication**: Support for multiple auth mechanisms (Bearer token, mTLS, API keys)\n1048: 2. **Authorization**: Verify user permissions before invoking agents\n1049: 3. **Input Validation**: Strict validation of payloads to prevent injection attacks\n1050: 4. **HTTPS Enforcement**: Require HTTPS for agent endpoints in production\n1051: 5. **Secret Management**: Secure handling of authentication tokens and API keys\n1052: 6. **Session Security**: Proper session ID generation and validation\n1053: 7. **Audit Logging**: Log all invocations for security auditing\n1054: 8. **Rate Limiting**: Protect against abuse with rate limiting\n1055: 9. **CORS Configuration**: Proper CORS settings for cross-origin requests\n1056: 10. **Secure Headers**: Automatically add security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options)\n1057: \n1058: ## Performance Considerations\n1059: \n1060: 1. **Connection Pooling**: Reuse HTTP connections for multiple invocations\n1061: 2. **Async I/O**: Use async/await for concurrent operations\n1062: 3. **Timeout Management**: Configurable timeouts for network operations\n1063: 4. **Caching**: Cache status results to reduce K8s API calls\n1064: 5. **Batch Operations**: Support for batch status checks\n1065: 6. **Lazy Loading**: Only initialize providers when needed\n1066: 7. **Resource Cleanup**: Proper cleanup of HTTP clients and connections\n1067: 8. **Memory Management**: Efficient handling of large payloads\n1068: 9. **Compression**: Support for request/response compression\n1069: 10. **Parallel Queries**: Query multiple K8s resources in parallel\n1070: \n1071: ## Appendix\n1072: \n1073: ### AgentRuntime CR Reference\n1074: \n1075: The AgentRuntime custom resource is defined as:\n1076: \n1077: ```yaml\n1078: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n1079: kind: AgentRuntime\n1080: metadata:\n1081:   name: agent-name\n1082:   namespace: default\n1083: spec:\n1084:   agentName: agent-name\n1085:   image: registry.example.com/agent:latest\n1086:   port: 8080\n1087:   replicas: 1\n1088:   env:\n1089:     - name: KEY\n1090:       value: value\n1091:   workloadManagerURL: http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\n1092:   routerURL: http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\n1093:   readinessProbe:\n1094:     path: /health\n1095:     port: 8080\n1096:   sessionTimeout: 15m\n1097:   maxSessionDuration: 8h\n1098: status:\n1099:   phase: Running\n1100:   agentEndpoint: http://agent-name.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\n1101:   replicas: 1\n1102:   availableReplicas: 1\n1103: ```\n1104: \n1105: ### Status Values\n1106: \n1107: | Status | Description | Exit Code |\n1108: |--------|-------------|-----------|\n1109: | `running` | Agent is running and ready to accept requests | 0 |\n1110: | `not_published` | Agent has not been published yet | 1 |\n1111: | `error` | Agent is in error state | 1 |\n1112: | `pending` | Agent is being deployed or updated | 0 |\n1113: | `created_no_status` | AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status | 0 |\n1114: | `not_found_in_k8s` | AgentRuntime CR not found in Kubernetes | 1 |\n1115: \n1116: ### Session Management\n1117: \n1118: Session IDs are managed as follows:\n1119: \n1120: 1. **Generation**: Session IDs are generated by the AgentCube runtime\n1121: 2. **Storage**: Session ID is stored in `metadata.session_id`\n1122: 3. **Transmission**: Session ID is sent via `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n1123: 4. **Lifecycle**: Sessions are managed by the AgentCube runtime based on TTL\n1124: 5. **Invocation**: Each invocation uses the current session ID from metadata\n1125: \n1126: ### Provider Comparison\n1127: \n1128: | Feature | AgentCube Provider | K8s Provider |\n1129: |---------|-------------------|--------------|\n1130: | Resource Type | AgentRuntime CR | Deployment + Service |\n1131: | Status Source | CR `.status` field | Deployment/Service status |\n1132: | URL Construction | Router-based | Service NodePort |\n1133: | Session Management | Built-in | Manual |\n1134: | Scalability | Auto-scaling via AgentCube | Manual replica management |\n1135: | Load Balancing | Router handles load | K8s Service handles load |\n1136: | Monitoring | Integrated with AgentCube | Standard K8s metrics |\n\n(End of file - total 1136 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status Commands Design Document\n\n**AR**: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令  \n**Module**: cmd/cli  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` and `status` commands are essential components of the AgentCube CLI that enable users to interact with deployed AI agents. The `invoke` command sends requests to published agent endpoints with optional payloads and custom headers, while the `status` command provides visibility into agent deployment state and health. Both commands support multiple providers: the AgentCube custom resource (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes resources (Deployment + Service).\n\n## Background\n\nAgentCube users need to interact with their deployed AI agents after the publish process completes. This includes:\n\n1. **Invocation**: Sending requests to agents with custom payloads, managing session IDs, and receiving responses\n2. **Status Monitoring**: Checking deployment health, endpoint availability, and runtime status\n3. **Multi-provider Support**: Working with both AgentCube CRs and standard Kubernetes deployments\n4. **Flexible Configuration**: Supporting custom headers, different payload formats, and provider-specific options\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/design.md","time":{"start":1775869974953,"end":1775869974976}}}}
