tcube\")\n33:   - [ ] verbose (default False)\n34: - [ ] Verify parameter types match design (str, bool)\n35: - [ ] Verify help text is present for all parameters\n36: - [ ] Verify command docstring describes functionality\n37: - [ ] Verify status output formatting is implemented\n38: \n39: **Verification**: Run `agentcube status --help` and verify all parameters are displayed correctly\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Task 3: Verify InvokeRuntime class structure\n44: - [ ] Verify InvokeRuntime class exists in agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py\n45: - [ ] Verify __init__ method with verbose and provider parameters\n46: - [ ] Verify logging is configured based on verbose flag\n47: - [ ] Verify class docstring describes functionality\n48: - [ ] Verify imports are correct (asyncio, httpx, logging, etc.)\n49: \n50: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.invoke_runtime import InvokeRuntime; r = InvokeRuntime(); print(r)\"` and verify it instantiates correctly\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### Task 4: Verify StatusRuntime class structure\n55: - [ ] Verify StatusRuntime class exists in agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py\n56: - [ ] Verify __init__ method with verbose and provider parameters\n57: - [ ] Verify logging is configured based on verbose flag\n58: - [ ] Verify class docstring describes functionality\n59: - [ ] Verify imports are correct (MetadataService, AgentCubeProvider, KubernetesProvider)\n60: \n61: **Verification**: Run `python -c \"from agentcube.runtime.status_runtime import StatusRuntime; r = StatusRuntime(); print(r)\"` and verify it instantiates correctly\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### Task 5: Verify InvokeRuntime.invoke method signature and structure\n66: - [ ] Verify invoke method accepts workspace_path: Path parameter\n67: - [ ] Verify invoke method accepts payload: Dict[str, Any] parameter\n68: - [ ] Verify invoke method accepts headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] parameter\n69: - [ ] Verify return type is Any\n70: - [ ] Verify method calls