esProvider instance\n149: - [ ] Verify method calls provider.get_agent_status\n150: - [ ] Verify method constructs status result dictionary with:\n151:   - [ ] status\n152:   - [ ] provider\n153:   - [ ] namespace\n154:   - [ ] deployment_name\n155:   - [ ] replicas\n156:   - [ ] ready_replicas\n157: - [ ] Verify method handles \"not_found\" status\n158: - [ ] Verify method handles partial readiness\n159: - [ ] Verify comprehensive error handling\n160: \n161: **Verification**: Run unit test for _get_k8s_status with mocked KubernetesProvider\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Task 11: Verify StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status method\n166: - [ ] Verify method accepts metadata parameter\n167: - [ ] Verify method checks agent_id exists\n168: - [ ] Verify method returns \"not_published\" if no agent_id\n169: - [ ] Verify method extracts namespace from metadata (default \"default\")\n170: - [ ] Verify method creates AgentCubeProvider instance\n171: - [ ] Verify method calls provider.get_agent_runtime\n172: - [ ] Verify method handles None return (CR not found)\n173: - [ ] Verify method extracts status from CR object\n174: - [ ] Verify method constructs status result dictionary with:\n175:   - [ ] status\n176:   - [ ] provider\n177:   - [ ] namespace\n178:   - [ ] agent_name\n179:   - [ ] agent_endpoint\n180:   - [ ] message\n181: - [ ] Verify method handles \"created_no_status\" state\n182: - [ ] Verify comprehensive error handling\n183: \n184: **Verification**: Run unit test for _get_cr_k8s_status with mocked AgentCubeProvider\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ### Task 12: Implement unit tests for InvokeRuntime.invoke\n189: - [ ] Create tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py\n190: - [ ] Test successful invoke with agentcube provider\n191: - [ ] Test successful invoke with k8s provider\n192: - [ ] Test missing agent_id and agent_endpoint raises ValueError\n193: - [ ] Test missing endpoint raises ValueError\n194: - [ ] Test session_id is added to headers\n195: - [ ] Test endpoint f