{"type":"text","timestamp":1775870500789,"sessionID":"ses_285e719caffed1lsPrEfzDjxoJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a214971001uZ7ShT6DpjZrvt","messageID":"msg_d7a2137a7001hEBHojjOWASlZy","sessionID":"ses_285e719caffed1lsPrEfzDjxoJ","type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented the AR-023 CLI invoke/status commands for the agentcube project. Here's what was completed:\n\n### ✅ Implementation Status\n\n**Core Functionality** (Already existed):\n- `InvokeRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` - handles agent invocation via HTTP\n- `StatusRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` - checks agent deployment status\n- CLI commands in `agentcube/cli/main.py` - `invoke()` and `status()` commands\n\n**Bug Fixes**:\n- Fixed operator precedence issue in endpoint extraction logic (line 70 in invoke_runtime.py)\n\n**Comprehensive Tests Created**:\n- `tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` - 23 tests covering all InvokeRuntime functionality\n- `tests/test_status_runtime.py` - 26 tests covering all StatusRuntime functionality\n\n### 📊 Test Results\n\n```\n✅ 172 tests passed\n✅ 5 tests skipped  \n✅ 92% coverage for invoke_runtime.py\n✅ 100% coverage for status_runtime.py\n```\n\n### 🎯 Key Features Implemented\n\n**Invoke Command**:\n- Supports JSON payload input\n- Custom HTTP headers support\n- Session ID management\n- Provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n- Endpoint formatting for AgentRuntime CR\n- Fallback to direct HTTP on errors\n\n**Status Command**:\n- AgentRuntime CR status checking\n- Standard Kubernetes deployment status\n- Provider selection\n- Error handling and graceful failures\n- Detailed status information (namespace, replicas, etc.)\n\n### 📁 Files Modified/Created\n\n**Modified**:\n- `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` - Fixed endpoint extraction bug\n- `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` - No changes needed\n\n**Created**:\n- `tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` - Comprehensive test suite\n- `tests/test_status_runtime.py` - Comprehensive test suite\n\n### ✅ Verification\n\nAll tests pass successfully and the code is ready for use with the existing CLI commands:\n- `agentcube invoke --payload '{}' --header 'X-Custom: value'`\n- `agentcube status --provider agentcube`","time":{"start":1775870500788,"end":1775870500788}}}
